{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, the RL algorithms that included diversity in their reward structures (RL PPO ED and RL A2C ED) demonstrated superior performance compared to their counterparts that relied solely on execution time.When compared to a baseline random algorithm, both GA and RL methods showed marked improvements in identifying WCET, affirming their robustness and reliability.",
    "Notably, RL algorithms outperformed GA in the CD case study, demonstrating their potential for superior exploration in complex environments.",
    "Additionally, the use of a simple program guided by domain expert heuristics further validated the RL algorithms' ability to identify the true WCET under predefined conditions.",
    "Chapter 6 Conclusion and Future WorkThis thesis has provided an examination of GA and RL within the context of estimating WCET for real-time systems.",
    "Through focused studies on CD and 6-DOF robotic scenarios, we have obtained insights that not only highlight the strengths and limitations of these methodologies but also suggest directions for future explorations in this critical area of research."
  ]
}